  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: The proposed roof extension by reason of its inappropriate design, siting, scale, bulk, height form and visual prominence would represent a visually dominant and discordant form of development when seen from the surrounding public and private realms. The proposal would disrupt an unaltered roofline and would be harmful to the architectural integrity of the host building, the wider terrace setting, the character and appearance of the New River Conservation Area, and the significance of the setting of the adjoining and surrounding  Grade II listed buildings. This is contrary to the objectives of the NPPF (2023), policy HC1 of the London Plan (2021), and policies PLAN1, DH1 and DH2 of Islington's Strategic and Development Management Policies (2023) as well as the guidance of Islington's Urban Design Guide (2017) and the New River Conservation Area Design Guidelines (2002)."
  ],
